{"title_page": "Zensar Technologies", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Zensar Technologies Ltd\n| logo = RPG_Zensar,_New_logo,_July_2017.png\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{Plainlist|\n* {{BSE|504067}}\n*{{NSE|ZENSARTECH}}\n* [[S&P]] BSE 500 component\n* Nifty 500 component\n}}\n| industry = [[IT services]]\n| key_people = Sandeep Kishore,<br /> CEO and [[Managing Director]]\n| services = [[Digital supply chain]], [[artificial intelligence]], [[cloud infrastructure]], [[data management]], [[enterprise applications]]\n| revenue = {{increase}}{{USD|566.9 million}} {{small|(2019)}}<ref name=zensar1>{{cite web | url = https://www.zensar.com/about-us/media/press-release/zensar-reports-202-growth-pat-and-176-growth-revenue-fy19 | publisher = Zensar | title = Zensar reports 202% growth and 176% growth in revenue | accessdate = 19 March 2020}}</ref>\n| num_employees = 11000+ (2019)\n| parent = [[RPG Group]]\n| website = {{url|www.zensar.com}}\n| caption = \n| foundation = 1991<ref name=Natarajan>{{cite book|author1=Ganesh Natarajan|author2=Prameela Kalive|title=From Start-Up to Global Success: The Zensar Story|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=imIlDAAAQBAJ|date=26 January 2016|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-93-5150-862-5}}</ref>\n| location = [[Pune, India]]\n}}\n'''Zensar Technologies Limited''' is a [[publicly traded]] software and services company with offices in 29 locations.<ref name = businessline>{{cite web | url = https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/info-tech/zensar-starts-operations-in-mexico-latam/article26733671.ece | publisher = The Hindu Businessline | title = Zensar starts operations in Mexico, LATAM | accessdate = 20 March 2020}}</ref> The company's stock trades on the [[Bombay Stock Exchange]] and on the [[National Stock Exchange of India]] under the [[ticker symbol]] ZENSARTECH.<ref name = bse>{{cite web | url = https://www.bseindia.com/stock-share-price/zensar-technologies-ltd/zensar-tech/504067/ | publisher = Bombay Stock Exchange | title = Zensar Technologies Stock | accessdate = 18 February 2020}}</ref> A subsidiary of [[RPG Group]], the company's chairman is [[Forbes India's richest Indian by year | Forbes-listed]] billionaire [[Harsh Goenka]].<ref name = businesstoday/>\n\n==History==\nZensar traces its origin to 1922 when a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[original equipment manufacturer | original-equipment manufacturing]] firm established a regional manufacturing unit in [[Pune, India]]. The firm evolved to become the Indian manufacturing arm of [[International Computers Limited|ICL]] and was re-named ICIM (International Computers Indian Manufacture). In 1963, ICIM listed on the [[Bombay Stock Exchange]]. In 1991, ICIM established a subsidiary company named [[International Computers Limited | International Computers Limited (ICIL)]], with a focus on [[software]]. In 1999, the original hardware division of ICIM was shuttered, leaving ICIM/ICIL as a purely software company. In February 2000, the company renamed to Zensar.<ref name=Natarajan /> Ganesh Natarajan became CEO in 2001, beginning a 15-year tenure.<ref name= \"Mumbai-Gold\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iitb.ac.in/alumni/en/awards/2017/distinguished-alumnus/dr-ganesh-natarajan|title=Alumni and Corporate Relations|id=Dr. Ganesh Natarajan|website=Indian Institute of Technology Bombay|access-date=13 October 2013 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20181013163657/http://www.iitb.ac.in/alumni/en/awards/2017/distinguished-alumnus/dr-ganesh-natarajan|archive-date=13 October 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> From 2000 to 2005, the company focused on [[application management]] for its clients.<ref name = startupzensar>{{cite book | publisher = SAGE Publications India | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=imIlDAAAQBAJ&pg | title = From Start-Up to Global Success: The Zensar Story | accessdate = 20 March 2020}}</ref> [[Vivek Gupta (businessman)|Vivek Gupta]] was named Zensar's Executive Chairman in 2010.<ref name=\"WBJ\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.wbjournal.com/article/20130618/METROWEST01/130619949|title=Post-Acquisition, Akibia Is Fully Assimilated|last=Pilon|first=Matt|date=2013-06-18|website=EBJ|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-07}}</ref> RPG Group, the Indian industrial conglomerate headquartered in [[Mumbai, Maharashtra]], is the majority shareholder in the company. Zensar is one of the RPG Group's companies and is now headquartered in [[Pune]] in Western India.\n\nBy 2012 Zensar had approximately 11000 employees servicing 400 clients in over 20 global locations<ref name=\"Bhide-thesis\">{{cite thesis|type=PhD|first1=Sachin Mohan|last1=Bhide|title=Study of change in composition and direction of exports by information technology companies in and around Pune |publisher=Savitribai Phule Pune University|date=2012|others=guide: Dr. M. R. Tambe|chapter=CHAPTER 6: Zensar Technologies Ltd. Case Study |chapter-url=http://shodhganga.inflibnet.ac.in:8080/jspui/bitstream/10603/185937/20/14_chapter%206.pdf |url=http://shodhganga.inflibnet.ac.in:8080/jspui/handle/10603/185937 |url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181014024059/http://shodhganga.inflibnet.ac.in:8080/jspui/bitstream/10603/185937/20/14_chapter%206.pdf|archive-date=14 October 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and at the end of the 2019 financial year earned revenues of over US$550 million.<ref name = zensar1/><ref name=\"ForbesI-20170418\">{{cite news|title=Zensar Technologies: On the digital highway|publisher=Forbes India|first1 =Aveek|last1=Datta|date=27 March 2019|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/boardroom/zensar-technologies-on-the-digital-highway/46707/1 |url-status= live| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320225158/http://www.forbesindia.com/article/boardroom/zensar-technologies-on-the-digital-highway/46707/1|archive-date=20 March 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSandeep Kishore was named Zensar's CEO in 2016, taking over from Ganesh Natarajan,<ref name=\"Mint-Kishore-1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/uFfhunnEhRZKZXJYjnBEYJ/Zensar-appoints-HCLs-Sandeep-Kishore-as-CEO-and-MD.html|title=Zensar appoints HCL\u2019s Sandeep Kishore as CEO and MD|last=Sanjai|first=P.R.|date=2015-12-14|publisher=HT Media Ltd|website=Livemint|access-date=2018-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011214449/https://www.livemint.com/Companies/uFfhunnEhRZKZXJYjnBEYJ/Zensar-appoints-HCLs-Sandeep-Kishore-as-CEO-and-MD.html|archive-date=11 October 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Mumbai-Gold\"/> with Zensar Technology backers being [[RPG Enterprises]]. In 2015, [[Apax Partners|APAX Portfolio Company]] acquired a stake in Zensar from Electra Partners Mauritius.<ref name=\"ForbesI-20170418\"/><ref name = businesstoday>{{cite web | url = https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/apax-partners-backed-firm-buys-stake-in-zensar-technologies/story/224637.html | publisher = Business Today | title = Apax Partners-backed firm buys 23.2% in Harsh Goenka's Zensar Technologies| accessdate = 20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Asof|October 2018}} Zensar Technologies has offices in over 20 countries.<ref name=\"NDTV\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/stock/zensar-technologies-ltd_zensartech/reports|title=Zensar Technologies Ltd.|id=Reports - History|website=NDTV Profit|access-date=14 October 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181014173807/https://www.ndtv.com/business/stock/zensar-technologies-ltd_zensartech/reports|archive-date=14 October 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It is listed on both the [[National Stock Exchange of India]] (NSE) and the [[Bombay Stock Exchange]] (BSE) and is a component of several [[Stock market index|indices]] including the NSE's Nifty 500 and the S&P BSE 500.<ref name=\"ET-Zensar-20181013\">{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/zensar-technologies-ltd/infocompanylisting/companyid-13597.cms |website=The Economic Times|title=ET Markets|id=Zensar Technologies Ltd |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20181013045552/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/zensar-technologies-ltd/infocompanylisting/companyid-13597.cms|archive-date=13 October 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Products and services == \nZensar\u2019s business is spread between North America, United Kingdom, parts of Europe and South Africa.<ref name = economictimes>{{cite web | url = https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/zensars-financial-services-focus-pays-off-in-south-africa/articleshow/71789707.cms | publisher = Economic Times | title = Zensar\u2019s financial services focus pays off in South Africa| accessdate = 20 March 2020}}</ref> Zensar\u2019s teams work out of 29 global locations including offices of acquired entities. Its primary business involves providing digital and technology solutions to global customers. Its key business verticals include high-tech manufacturing, retail and consumer services, financial services and emerging services.<ref name = economictimes2>{{cite web | url = https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/zensar-trims-retail-portfolio-to-focus-better-on-core/articleshow/73603633.cms | publisher = Economic Times | title = Zensar trims retail portfolio, to focus better on core | accessdate = 20 March 2020}}</ref> \n\n==Acquisitions==\nThe following is a list of acquisitions made by Zensar since 2005.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ style=\"text-align: left;\" | {{nowrap|Ventures}}\n|-\n! Venture !! Date !! Company !! Value !! Location base !! Description\n|-\n| Acquisition || 2018 || Cynosure INC || US$33m || US || For leverage of insurance and Guidewire practice.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/zensar-to-acquire-cynosure-for-33-mn/articleshow/63400515.cms|title=Zensar to acquire Cynosure for $33 mn|date=2018-03-21|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2018-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archi