{"title_page": "List of Filipino generals in the Philippine Revolution and the Philippine\u2013American War", "text_new": "This is a compendium of the [[Philippines|Filipino]] generals, commanders and  who fought during the [[Philippine Revolution]], [[Filipino-American War]] and the Post-war insurgencies against U.S occupation of the Philippines.\n\n==General Officers==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"leaders\n|-\n|+ Filipino Generals in the Philippine Revolution of 1896 and the Filipino-American War of 1899\n|-\n!Name\n!\n!Grade{{ref|a|a}}\n!Affiliation{{ref|b|b}}\n!Province{{ref|c|c}}\n|-\n|[[Gregorio Aglipay]][[File:Gregorio Aglipay.jpg|thumb|Gregorio Aglipay]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"0\"|\n*Vicario General Castrence (Military Vicar General)  \n*Founder of the group called as Liwanag (Light), an auxiliary of the Katipunan\n*Founder and Supreme Bishop of the \"Philippine Independent Church\"\n|\n*Katipunan-Liwanag\n*First Philippine Republic\n|\n*[[Victoria, Tarlac]]\n* Military campaigns in Ilocos Norte\n|-\n|[[Baldomero Aguinaldo]][[File:Baldomero Aguinaldo.jpg|thumb|Baldomero Aguinaldo]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"3\"|\n*Lieutenant General\n*Commander of general of the revolutionary forces in the southern Luzon provinces (1901)\n*[[First Philippine Republic]] (1898-1901)- Secretary of War and Marine\n*[[Revolutionary Government of the Philippines]] (1898\u20131899)- Secretary of War and Public Works\n*[[Republic of Biak-na-Bato]] (1897) - Secretary of Treasury \n*[[Tejeros Convention]]-Tejeros Revolutionary Government(1897) - Director of Finance\n*President of [[Magdalo Council- Katipunan]]\n|\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Revolutionary Government of the Philippines\n*Republic of Biak-na-Bato\n*Tejeros Revolutionary Government\n*[[Magdalo (Katipunan faction)]] \n|[[Cavite]]\n|-\n|[[Crispulo Aguinaldo]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"2\"|[[Major General]]\n|Magdalo\n|Cavite\n|-\n|[[Emilio Aguinaldo]][[File:Emilio Aguinaldo ca. 1919 (Restored).jpg|thumb|Emilio Aguinaldo ca. 1919 (Restored)]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"5\"|[[Field Marshal]]/General and Commander-in-chief of the \"Philippine Republican Army\" (President of the \"[[Malolos Republic]]\")<ref>{{Harvnb|Zaide|Zaide|1999|pp=239, 247}}.</ref>\n|Magdalo\n|Cavite\n|-\n|[[Jose Alejandrino]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Brigadier General\n*He was a contributor to [[La Solidaridad]] and one of the members of the Propaganda Movement in Spain along with Jose Rizal, Marcelo H. del Pilar, Mariano Ponce and Graciano Lopez Jaena\n*He was part of Aguinaldo's [[Hong Kong Junta]], the exiled Revolutionary Government of the Philippines\n*Along with Felipe Agoncillo, Jos\u00e9 Maria Basa and Mariano Ponce, he helped organised the ''Consejo Revolucion''\n|\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Republic of Biak-Na-Bato\n*Revolutionary Government of the Philippines\n*Katipunan\n|Family from [[Arayat, Pampanga]] \n|-\n|[[Felix Ali\u00f1o]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"| \n*Katipunan General<ref name=\"sunstar1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sunstar.com.ph/article/1820390 |title=Talisay's Ali\u00f1o brothers honored \n|author=<!--Not stated--> |date=August 26, 2019 |website=SunStar Cebu |publisher=SunStar Publishing Inc. \n|quote=the Ali\u00f1o brothers started the uprising against Spain in Talisay, then a municipality, a day before the Battle of Tres Abril}}</ref>\n*Brother Hilaro Ali\u00f1o was another Katipunan General\n*Brothers Potenciano and Sulpicio Ali\u00f1o were also active members of the Philippine revolution in the Visayas\n|\n*Katipunan in Cebu\n*Cebu Revolutionary Government\n*First Philippine Republic\n|[[Talisay,Cebu]]\n|-\n|[[Hilario Ali\u00f1o]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"| \n*Katipunan General<ref name=\"sunstar1\"/>\n*Brother Felix Ali\u00f1o was another Katipunan General\n*Brothers Potenciano and Sulpicio Ali\u00f1o were also active members of the Philippine revolution in the Visayas\n|\n*Katipunan in Cebu\n*Cebu Revolutionary Government\n*First Philippine Republic\n|[[Talisay,Cebu]]\n|-\n|[[Elias Angeles]][[File:General Elias Angeles.tif|thumb|General Elias Angeles]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Brigadier General\n*Commander of Guerilla Forces In Bicol Region<ref>{{cite book |last=Worcester |first=Dean Conant |date=January 1, 1930 |title=The Philippines Past and Present, Volume 1|publisher=The Macmillan Co.|page=215|author-link=Dean Conant Worcester}}</ref>\n|\n*First Philippine Republic\n|Ambos, Camarines\n|-\n|[[Mariano \u00c1lvarez]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"3\"|Lieutenant General (President, Magdiwang Council)<ref>{{Harvnb| Alvarez|1992|pp=[https://books.google.com/books?id=F3q\u2013krDckHwC&pg=PA7 7], [https://books.google.com/books?id=F3q\u2013krDckHwC&pg=PA127 127]}} (confirms General Officer status, but not specific grade).</ref>\n|[[Magdiwang (Katipunan faction)|Magdiwang]]\n|Cavite\n|-\n|[[Santiago Alvarez (Filipino General)|Santiago Alvarez]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|Brigadier General (Captain General, Magdiwang Army)\n|Magdiwang\n|Cavite\n|-\n|[[Pascual Alvarez]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|Brigadier General<ref>{{Harvnb| Alvarez|1992|p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=F3q\u2013krDckHwC&pg=PA116 116]}} (confirms General Officer status, but not specific grade).</ref>\n|Magdiwang\n|Cavite\n|-\n|[[Vicente Alvarez]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"3\"|\n*Lieutenant General\n*Datu Tumanggung (Royal Marshall of Camp) - title bestowed by the Sultan of Sulu\n*Governor-General Diego de los R\u00edos was defeated by the forces of General Vicente Alvarez in Fort Pilar (April 1899) \n|\n*Katipunan in Cebu\n*First Philippine Republic\n*[[Republic of Zamboanga]]\n|\n*[[Zamboanga (province)|Zamboanga]]\n*Guerrilla campaign against U.S in Basilan and Misamis provinces\n|-\n|[[Servillano Aquino]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|General\n|\n*First Philippine Republic\n|[[Pampanga]]\n|-\n|[[Juan Araneta]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|General\n|\n|[[Negros (island)|Negros]]\n|-\n|[[Pablo S. Araneta]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|Brigadier General, Commanding General of the Panay Revolutionary Forces, Chief of the Expeditionary Forces of the Federal Republic of the Visayas\n|[[Republic of Negros]], [[Federal State of the Visayas]]\n|[[Panay]],[[Iloilo]]\n|-\n|[[Marcelino Aure]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|Brigadier General\n|Magdiwang\n|Cavite\n|-\n|[[Ram\u00f3n Avance\u00f1a]][[File:Ramon Avancena.jpg|thumb|Ramon Avancena]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|Brigadier General<ref>{{cite book |last=Cruz |first=Isagani A. |date= 2000|title=Res Gestae: A Brief History of the Supreme Court |location=Philippines|publisher=Rex Book Store, Manila}}</ref>\n|? \n|[[Iloilo]]\n|-\n|[[Hermogenes Bautista]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|Brigadier General<ref>{{Harvnb| Alvarez|1992|p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=F3q\u2013krDckHwC&pg=PA149 149]}} (confirms General Officer status, but not specific grade).</ref>\n|\n*Pro-Andr\u00e9s Bonifacio\n*[[Magdiwang (Katipunan faction)]]\n|[[Bayanbayanan, Marikina]]\n|-\n|[[Vito Belarmino]][[File:General Vito Belarmino.tif|thumb|General Vito Belarmino]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"2\"|Major General<ref>{{Harvnb|Linn|2000|p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=-5WOrmt_VxcC&pg=PA97 97]}}</ref>\n|Magdalo\n|Cavite\n|-\n|[[Ramon Bernardo]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Katipunan General<ref name=alvarezp20>{{Harvnb| Alvarez|1992|p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=F3q\u2013krDckHwC&pg=PA20 20]}}</ref>\n* One of the Commanding generals in the [[Battle of San Juan del Monte]] (August 30, 1896)\n|Katipunan-Magdiwang\n|Pandacan, Manila\n|-\n|[[Andr\u00e9s Bonifacio]] [[File:Gat Andr\u00e9s Bonifacio.jpg|thumb|Andr\u00e9s Bonifacio]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"5\"|\n*One of the founding fathers of the [[Katipunan]]\n*Supremo (Head) of the Katipunan <ref>{{Citation | last1 =Guerrero | first1 =Milagros | last2 =Encarnacion | first2 =Emmanuel | last3 =Villegas | first3 =Ramon | title =Andr\u00e9s Bonifacio and the 1896 Revolution | journal =Sulyap Kultura | volume = 1 | issue =2 | pages =3\u201312 | publisher =National Commission for Culture 