igbac\n*Brigadier General<ref name=\"Eyot1904\">{{cite book|author=Canning Eyot|title=The Story of the Lopez Family: A Page from the History of the War in the Philippines|url=https://archive.org/details/cu31924023262938|year=1904|publisher=J.H. West Company|page=[https://archive.org/details/cu31924023262938/page/n25 20]}}</ref>\n|\n*Katipunan in Lipa\n*First Philippine Republic\n*General Malvar's Tagalog Republic \n|[[Lipa, Batangas]]\n|-\n|[[Le\u00f3n Kilat]]\n|\n|{{sort|3|Lieutenant General}}\n|\n|[[Cebu]]\n|-\n|[[Agueda Kahabagan]][[File:General Agueda Kahabagan.tif|thumb|General Agueda Kahabagan-The only woman general officially listed in the roster of the First Philippine Republic]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Brigadier General<ref>{{cite web|url=http://malacanang.gov.ph/3622-artemio-ricarte-on-the-arrest-and-execution-of-bonifacio/|title=Artemio Ricarte on the Arrest and Execution of Bonifacio - Presidential Museum and Library|publisher=}}</ref>\n*\"Henerala Agueda\" was appointed as the only woman in the roster of generals in the army of the [[First Philippine Republic]]\n*''(Note:  The image is a conceptual illustration or artist rendition of historical figure based on composite models and historical images. There are no known public images or illustration of the subject matter at present.)''\n|\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Tagalog Republic under [[Miguel Malvar]]\n|Laguna\n|-\n|[[Aniceto Lacson]]\n|\n|{{sort|2|Major General}}\n|Neutral\n|[[Negros (island)|Negros]]\n|-\n|[[Urbano Lacuna]]\n|\n|{{sort|1|Brigadier General<ref>{{Harvnb|Linn|2000|pp=[https://books.google.com/books?id=-5WOrmt_VxcC&pg=PA64 64], [https://books.google.com/books?id=-5WOrmt_VxcC&pg=PA196 196] (notes 16, 17, 20, 21 & 24)}}</ref>}}\n|Neutral\n|[[Nueva Ecija]]\n|-\n|[[Pascual V. Ledesma]]\n|\n|{{sort|1|Commanding General<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pinoyfolktales.blogspot.com/2013/01/filipino-martyr-pascual-v-ledesma.html |title=Filipino Martyr: PASCUAL V. LEDESMA |author=<!--Not state