o Mayo]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Commander<ref name=\"InstituteAsian2002\">{{cite book|author1=New York University. Asian/Pacific/American Studies Program and Institute|author2=New York University Asian|author3=Pacific|title=Vestiges of War: The Philippine-American War and the Aftermath of an Imperial Dream 1899-1999|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1v48DAAAQBAJ&pg=PA6|date=December 2002|publisher=NYU Press|isbn=978-0-8147-9791-4|pages=6\u201310}}</ref> of Tiaong-Candelaria Guerrilla Column-Banahaw Battalion of General Miguel Malvar's Tagalog Republic\n*\"de facto general\" when General Miguel Malvar surrendered in April 13, 1902\n*Lt. Colonel - First Philippine Republic\n|\n*\"Army of Liberation\" of General Miguel Malvar\n*Tagalog Republic of General Miguel Malvar\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Revolutionary Government of the Philippines\n*Katipunan in Batangas\n|[[Tiaong]] and [[Candelaria, Quezon|Candelaria]] in Quezon Province, [[Lipa, Batangas]]\n|-\n|[[Raymundo Melliza]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"| \n*General\n*Second President of Federal State of the Visayas (January 17, 1899) after General Roque Lopez\n|\n*Federal State of the Visayas\n*Cebu Revolutionary Government\n*First Philippine Republic\n|[[Molo, Iloilo City|Molo]], Iloilo\n|-\n|[[Alejo Nazareno Mi\u00f1osa]][[File:General Alejo Nazareno Mi\u00f1osa.tif|thumb|General Alejo Nazareno Mi\u00f1osa]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Brigadier General\n*General Alejo Nazareno Mi\u00f1osa- Cebuano general and hero who helped General Leon Kilat in battle against Spanish rule in Cebu\n|\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Federated States of Visayas\n*Revolutionary Provisional Government in Cebu\n*Katipunan in Cebu\n|Cebu\n|-\n|[[Ambrosio Rodrin Mojica]][[File:General Ambrosio Mojica.tif|thumb|General Ambrosio Mojica-One of the commanding Generals of Leyte and Samar regions]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n* Capitan Municipal of Indang, Cavite <ref>{{cite journal |last1=Amascual III |first1=Pablo U.|date=2003|