is Lea (judge)|George Harris Lea]]\n|votes =2,721\n|percentage =42.8\n|change = &minus;5.8\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n|votes =916\n|percentage =14.4\n|change = +14.1\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n|votes =6,358\n|percentage =91.0\n|change = &minus;2.1 (est)\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n |reg. electors = 6,988\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link\n|winner =Conservative Party (UK)\n|swing = +5.8\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Election box begin| title=[[1883 Wigan by-election|By-election, 21 Dec 1883]]: Wigan (1 seat)<ref name=\"craig1832\"/>\n}}\n{{Election box candidate unopposed with party link|\n|party =Conservative Party (UK)\n|candidate = [[Nathaniel Eckersley]]\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link no swing|\n|winner =Conservative Party (UK)\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n* Caused by Knowles' death.\n\n{{Election box begin| title=[[1882 Wigan by-election|By-election, 4 Dec 1882]]: Wigan (1 seat)<ref name=\"craig1832\"/>\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party =Conservative Party (UK)\n|candidate = [[Algernon Egerton]]\n|votes = 2,867\n|percentage = 56.1\n|change = +4.6\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party =Liberal Party (UK)\n|candidate = [[Walter Wren]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Wigan Election|url=https://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk/viewer/bl/0001940/18821208/103/0009|accessdate=15 December 2017|work=Todmorden & District News|date=8 December 1882|page=9|via = [[British Newspaper Archive]]|url-access=subscription }}</ref>\n|votes = 2,243\n|percentage = 43.9\n|change = &minus;4.7\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n|votes = 624\n|percentage = 12.2\n|change = +11.9\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n|votes = 5,110\n|percentage = 83.8\n|change = &minus;9.3 (est)\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n |reg. electors = 6,097\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n|winner =Conservative Party (UK)\n|swing = +4.7\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n* Caused by the previous election being declared void on petition.\n\n{{Ele